Journalism in USA 2023: Eligibility, Universities, Document Requirements, Application Process & Scholarship

  • 1101 Reads
  • 3 min Read
  • By:CANAM Group
  • Updated On:May 19,2023 11:03 AM IST

Journalism in the USA is a crucial industry that offers students diverse career opportunities and high-quality academic experiences. Journalism in the USA has various specializations, such as reporting, editing, anchoring, producing, and managing. While pursuing a degree in journalism in the USA can be expensive, the country has some of the world's top-ranking journalism colleges that make it an attractive destination for international students.

Journalism involves various skills, such as reporting, editing, anchoring, producing, and managing. The primary focus of a journalism degree is to train students to investigate and report on local and global events truthfully and ethically.

Journalism in USA is a critical industry that shares responsibility for disseminating news and keeping people updated about the happenings worldwide. Students can pursue different specialisations in journalism colleges to study in USA. These programs typically span four years for undergraduate and two years for postgraduate studies.

However, the cost of pursuing a degree in journalism can be high, with an average of around $40,000 per annum for undergraduate studies and $30,000 per annum for postgraduate studies.

USA is home to some of the world's top-ranking journalism colleges, per the QS Ranking 2022. It is a popular destination for international students seeking quality education in this field.

Why Study Journalism in USA?

International students are attracted to study in USA for journalism because they offer immense career opportunities and a high-quality academic experience. According to the US Bureau of Labour Statistics, the job outlook for reporters and journalists is expected to grow by 12% from 2018 to 2028. Additionally, journalists with master's degrees in the US earn an average of $17,000 more annually than those with only a bachelor's degree, and a 12% salary increase can be expected every 16 months.

Furthermore, media and communication occupations are projected to grow by 4% by 2028, providing further job opportunities for journalism graduates. Journalism in USA has competitive hourly wages across various industries, such as broadcasting and publishing.

The US is also home to many of the world's top universities, with New York and California having the highest number of publicly funded universities. This makes it an attractive destination for international students, who account for 1.1 million of the 4.4 million international students globally. India is the top country of origin for international students to study in USA, representing 17.3% of the total number of international students.

Journalism in USA: Eligibility

  • Duration of the course: 4 years
  • Minimum 50% aggregate marks are required for student’s with 10+2 level
  • Minimum ACT score of 22

English Proficiency Test Requirements

  • TOEFL (PBT): 550–650
  • TOEFL (iBT): 79–100
  • IELTS: 6–7

Required Documents

  • Academic transcripts of grades 10 and 12 from a recognised university.
  • The certificates of IELTS and TOEFL exams as proof of knowledge of the English language
  • A copy of passport
  • A statement of purpose stating candidate’s intention of coming to USA
  • A letter of recommendation from the professors of the previous institution studied

Journalism in USA: Eligibility

Duration of the course: 2 years
Undergraduate degree with minimum GPA of 3.0 on a 4.0 scale (83% - 86%)

Minimum GRE score requirement:

1)Quantitative Reasoning: 153
2)Verbal Reasoning: 150
3)Analytical Writing: 3.5

English Proficiency Test Requirements

1)IELTS - 6.5
2)TOEFL (iBT) -90

Required Documents

Academic transcripts of grades 10, 12, and bachelor's degree from a recognised university
The certificates of IELTS and TOEFL exams for proof of knowledge of the English language
A copy of the student’s passport
A statement of purpose stating their intention of coming to USA
A letter of recommendation from the professors of the previous institution studied or from immediate senior of the current workplace
A 750-word autobiography
A 1000-word statement of goals
Proof of financial support

How to Get Admission in Journalism in USA?


1.Check Eligibility: Check the university's official website to determine whether a student meets the eligibility requirements for the desired program.

2.Submit Application: Apply online to study journalism in USA in 2023, along with the application fee.

3.Upload Supporting Documents: Follow the procedure for uploading the supporting documents, including transcripts, test scores, essays, letters of recommendation, and a resume/CV required to study in USA.

4.Check Application Status: Always check the official website to find out if the application for journalism in USA 2023 has been approved.

5.Respond to Admission Offer: Respond to the mail immediately after a student receives the acceptance letter from a desired university/college. Accept the offer before the deadline to secure a spot to study in USA.

6.Enroll in the University: Enroll and pay the tuition deposit to guarantee your seat.

7.Apply for Study Permit: Following confirmation of acceptance, proceed with the application for a study permit required for international students.
It is important to note that each university's application process may vary slightly, so always check the specific requirements and deadlines for each university/college you are interested in applying.

Application Process to Apply at Journalism Universities in USA

Applying to journalism in USA involves a multi-step process that requires careful preparation and attention to detail. Here is a general outline of the steps to take:

  • Start by exploring different universities and consider factors like the courses offered, faculty expertise, opportunities for hands-on experience, institute location, and the success of its graduates
  • Check the program eligibility and specific academic requirements for each university
  • Often for undergraduate admissions, students are required to take standardised tests like the SAT or ACT or English proficiency tests like the TOEFL or IELTS
  • Fill out the application form submitting the necessary personal and academic information
  • Submit important documents like academic transcripts, SOP, LOR, and resume (if required)
  • Before making an application fee payment, check whether the institute offers fee waivers for students who demonstrate financial need
  • Prepare for interviews conducted by the admission authority as part of the application process
  • Students looking for financial assistance can start researching financial aid options like scholarships, grants, bursaries and more
  • Make sure to submit application before the admission deadlines

Career Opportunities After Journalism in USA

Graduating with a degree in journalism opens doors to many career opportunities for students. Some of the common career paths for journalism graduates are:

  • Reporter/Journalist
  • Editor
  • Broadcast Journalist
  • Photojournalist
  • Foreign Correspondent
  • Freelance Writer
  • Public Relations Specialist
  • Social Media Manager
  • Content Writer/Strategist
  • Investigative Journalist
  • Data Journalist
  • Communications Director

Conclusion

Journalism in USA offer numerous benefits to students, including excellent career opportunities, quality education, and competitive wages. However, applying to top American universities is not as easy as it seems. This is why it is suggested that students should seek guidance from study abroad consultants in making an error-free application.

FAQ

What is the duration of a bachelors degree in Journalism in the USA?

The duration of a bachelors degree in Journalism in the USA is four years.

What is the duration of a masters degree in Journalism in the USA?

The duration of a masters degree in Journalism in the USA is two years.

What is the highest-paying position in journalism in the United States?

Senior reporters, correspondents, and news analysts often earn the highest salaries in journalism.

Which are the top recruiting companies after journalism in the USA?

Some are the top recruiting companies after Journalism in the USA are New York Times, CNN, Nexstar Broadcasting Group, NBC, and Bloomberg LP.
